				<wikidot:authorName>AnActualCrow</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6040770</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>My biggest problem with this is that most of the narrative-relevant information in this only appears in the conversation in the last offset. I think this is in large part due to the 1st offset, which doesn't add too much to what readers already know from the initial page. I'd get rid of the initial page and start on the 1st offset.</p> <p>I'm a bit conflicted on bit about the invention of zepplins. While it is sort of interesting, it's completely disconnected from the rest of the article.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
